	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Two videos posted on Facebook by the Intelligence Bureau SA shows a cash-in-transit heist on an armoured vehicle on the N12 highway near Rondebult Road. Rapid response from police officials caused the attackers to escape empty handed.WATCH Durban – Police are investigating a case of business robbery after a group of armed men robbed two stores at the Westwood Mall in Westville, Durban, on Monday morning. Seven armed men held two security guards and a cleaner at gunpoint after they forcefully gained entrance to the mall at about 01:30, said Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane. "They then smashed open the glass doors of two stores inside the mall. They took jewellery, clothing, cellphones and perfumes, before fleeing the scene in their getaway vehicle," said Zwane. No arrests had been made yet, he said. "A case of business robbery is being investigated by Westville SAPS," Zwane said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  